  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>cauliflower[s]</strong> into small florets and separate any<strong> </strong>leaves<strong> </strong>from the stem[s]</p><p>Discard the stem[s] and keep the leaves</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into small, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658829571731-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658829571731-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658829571731-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658829571731-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658829571731-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>cauliflower florets</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a large pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 12-15 min</p><p>Once everything is fork-tender and easy to mash, drain and set aside</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658829575846-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658829575846-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658829575846-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658829575846-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1658829575846-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>cauliflower leaves </strong>and <strong>remaining cauliflower florets</strong> to a large baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until the cauliflower is golden and the leaves are crispy</p><p>Peel and finely chop your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong> and<strong> ginger</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1658829579899-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1658829579899-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1658829579899-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1658829579899-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1658829579899-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add<strong> </strong>most of the <strong>chopped onion</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5 min or until softened</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!), then dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and<strong> chopped<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>creamed coconut </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1658829588549-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1658829588549-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1658829588549-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1658829588549-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1658829588549-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger </strong>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> and cook for 2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>drained potato & cauliflower florets</strong> with the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and mash until smooth but still retaining some texture</p><p>Add your <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas </strong>and the<strong> </strong>juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong> and cook for 2 min further</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1658829597019-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1658829597019-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1658829597019-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1658829597019-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1658829597019-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>brioche halves </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through and lightly golden – this is your <strong>chilli brioche</strong></p><p>Tip: For a little extra indulgence, top the warmed chilli brioche with your favourite butter alternative</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1658829604511-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1658829604511-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1658829604511-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1658829604511-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1658829604511-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add most of the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(save some for garnish!) to the pan and stir it all together</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min further or until thickened to a bolognese-like consistency – this is your <strong>cauliflower pav bhaji</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1658829612037-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1658829612037-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1658829612037-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1658829612037-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1658829612037-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> cauliflower pav bhaji</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> golden cauliflower</strong> and <strong>crispy cauliflower leaves</strong> and serve the <strong>chilli brioche</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>red onion</strong> and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
